|*******************************************************************************
| TEXAS INSTRUMENTS INCORPORATED
| Standard Linear and Logic Group
| IBIS Model of SN74LVC1G04
| SINGLE INVERTER GATE
| This file contains package information for the following:
|  SON 6-pin (DSF) package as [Component] LVC1G04_DSF
|  SOT 5-pin (DCK) package as [Component] LVC1G04_DCK
|  SOT 5-pin (DBV) package as [Component] LVC1G04_DBV
|  NanoStar WCSP 5-pin (YEA) package as [Component] LVC1G04_YEA
|  NanoFree WCSP 5-pin (YZA) package as [Component] LVC1G04_YZA
|  NanoStar WCSP 5-pin (YEP) package as [Component] LVC1G04_YEP
|  NanoFree WCSP 5-pin (YZP) package as [Component] LVC1G04_YZP
| This device can be powered at the following Vccs:
|  1.8 volt Vcc
|  2.5 volt Vcc
|  3.3 volt Vcc
|  5 volt Vcc
| This file provides unique models under the [Model Selector] for each Vcc.
| For operation at a specific Vcc, select the appropriate model after each
| [Model Selector] keyword.
|*******************************************************************************
|
[IBIS Ver]      3.2
[Comment char]  |_char
[File Name]     sn74lvc1g04.ibs
[File Rev]      1.4 | d_die
[Date]          03/05/2014 
[Source]        
| Texas Instruments Incorporated.
| Analog-eLab Design Center, HPA
| 12500 TI Blvd
| Dallas, TX -75243
|
[Notes]         Revision History:
| The following is an IBIS list for the SN74LVC1G04.
| Please contact sllibis@ti.com with questions and
| comments concerning SLL IBIS models.
| - FILE REV HISTORY
| - 1.2 YEA, YZA, YEP, and YZP packages added on 08/17/04
| - The SN74LVC1G04 inputs have no power clamp diode. 
|   Therefore, the input power clamp data has been deleted.
| - Due to the fact that the Device is 5.5-V Input tolarent, 
|   the pulldown model has some Non-Monotonic Warnings.
| - End point warning due to AC and DC mismatch.
| - 1.3 Modified R_load to 50 ohm for rising/falling data
| - 1.4 DSF package added 03/05/2014.
|
